The paper focuses on introducing a novel approach to improve the performance of deep neural networks for visual recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the benefits of introducing second-order operations into deep neural networks, which falls under the category of optimization and learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the proposed approach involves modifying the network architecture, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach on various datasets, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL).
